							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/franlittlewood/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/fran-littlewood-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/fran-littlewood-300x300.jpeg 2x" alt="Fran Littlewood" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/franlittlewood/">Fran Littlewood</a></h6>
										Fran Littlewood has an MA in creative writing from Royal Holloway, University of London. Before her MA, she worked as a journalist, including a stint at the <em>Times</em>. She lives in London with her husband and their three daughters. <em>Amazing Grace Adams</em> is her debut novel.																			</div>
